en_404877_0	The opening of four school buildings and a sports pavilion with the ground within the Maharagama electorate took place under the patronage of President Maithriapla Sirisena this morning.
en_404877_1	The President declared open today the new buildings of the President College in Maharagama, the Mahragama Central College, the Kottawa Dharmapala Vidyalaya and the Kotte Madiwela Schools.
en_404877_2	President Maithripala Sirisena who first arrived at the Maharagama President’s College was accorded a very warm welcome by the students.
en_404877_3	After unveiling the plaque, the President vested in the students the fully equipped new auditorium.
en_404877_4	Later the President undertook an inspection visit.
en_404877_5	On this occasion the President was presented with a memento.
en_404877_6	Later the President arrived at the Maharagama Central College.
en_404877_7	The President declared open the fully fledged auditorium constructed with financial grants of the Western Province built under the concept *the best things are for the children.”
en_404877_8	President Maithripala Sirisena who arrived at the Kottawa Dharmapala Vidyalaya was accorded a rousing welcome by the students.
en_404877_9	Thereafter he vested in the students the fully fledged auditorium constructed at the school.
en_404877_10	The President thereafter vested in the public the fully fledged Isuru Devapriya sports pavilion constructed in the Mirihana area in Kotte on behalf of the young men and women of the area.
en_404877_11	The Western Provincial Council had taken the initiative of transforming the Kotte Madiwela Sri Rahula Maha Vidyalaya into the first smart school of the country.
en_404877_12	Accordingly the President declared open the four storeyed building comprising the smart classrooms.
en_404877_13	Meanwhile the President declared open the Janajaya City Super Market Complex built by the Kotte Municipal Council.
en_404877_14	It has ten storeys and is equipped with all facilities.
en_404877_15	The expenditure incurred on the complex was 2000 million rupees.
en_404877_16	After unveiling the plaque the President undertook an inspection visit to the building.
